analysisPopulations.text: All participants who were enrolled in the study

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: All enrolled participants who received at least one dose of ALXN1840 and have at least one post-baseline efficacy assessment
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All enrolled participants who received at least one dose of ALXN1840 and have at least one post-baseline efficacy assessment
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled AND received >=1 dose of ALXN1840 AND has >=1 post-baseline efficacy assessment

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.text: All participants in the Full Analysis Set who completed the study without major protocol deviations that could affect the efficacy assessments
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All participants in the Full Analysis Set who completed the study without major protocol deviations that could affect the efficacy assessments
analysisPopulations.criteria: In FAS AND completed study AND no major protocol deviations affecting efficacy

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Set
analysisPopulations.text: All enrolled participants who received at least one dose of ALXN1840
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All enrolled participants who received at least one dose of ALXN1840
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled AND received >=1 dose of ALXN1840

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: All participants in the Safety Set who have at least one evaluable pharmacokinetic sample
analysisPopulations.label: PK
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All participants in the Safety Set who have at least one evaluable pharmacokinetic sample
analysisPopulations.criteria: In Safety Set AND has >=1 evaluable PK sample

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacodynamic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: All participants in the Safety Set who have at least one evaluable pharmacodynamic sample
analysisPopulations.label: PD
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: All participants in the Safety Set who have at least one evaluable pharmacodynamic sample
analysisPopulations.criteria: In Safety Set AND has >=1 evaluable PD sample
